cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.RO 

The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks (DNN) for predicting stock-outs in multi-echelon supply chains. This involves analyzing large amounts of data and making predictions based on complex relationships between different nodes and time periods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with systems and control, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics).
